						               													<description>Competitive card-driven tactical combat from 2 to 4 players. Prepare to dominate and take control.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Exsilium is a fast and light game with simple rules and familiar mechanics. Players will use Deckbuilding to upgrade their decks and battle enemy factions for control the Baralytas crystals.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;All players will start with 12 basic cards and draw 4 at the start of each turn. Each player can perform as many actions as there are cards in his hand and can decide between activating the action of the card or using it to move the miniatures of his faction.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Expand the territory to wherever you want. Exsilium is competitive, so ruthless and terrible tactics are welcome.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;All against all, without exception.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In Exsilium you must survive both the other factions and the common enemy that has emerged from the depths of Eris. A.I. enemies allow even in two player games, the battle starts from the first second.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;RULE ERIS!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Control Terminal points and upgrade your deck before the other factions. Cross the frontiers, dominate the crystals and take control of the dwarf planet.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Exsilium's mechanics allow you to place explosive mines on the ground, drop items, and use tactics to mislead A.I. enemies.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Don't forget that you have a 24-page manual where you can explore each rule in detail and make the most of your abilities in battle.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The preparation of the game is super fast and the duration for 4 players does not exceed 50 minutes.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
